
Pre-requisite:

manifest.json should be put in your project/web folder

You will need to create an extension on google chrome using the following link (Rob Donovan's answer)
https://superuser.com/questions/224500/how-to-display-local-images-in-chrome-using-file-protocol


Add all the .jpg (images) from the Images folder on the repository and .jsp files in your project/web folder. 
Take care when you create a new jsp file (webpage) to change the path to project/web

index.jsp is the homepage that starts on the browser

Still needs checking:
using the java bean class, to read the input from the user
and integrating with the database

Note: if glassfish version 4.1.1 is giving you errors (unfixed bugs), downgrade to version 4.1.0 
